The paper deals with erasure-correcting codes and their application in distributed storage systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Distributed Systems (cs.DS), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between minimum distance and dimension of codes, which is a topic of interest in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
